src: tɕe [kɯpɤz nɯ mɯ-ɲɯ-kɤ-βzu kɤ-nɯmga], iʑɤra, ji-mthɯm nɯra <binggui> tu-χtɯ-j tɕe nɯ ɯ-ŋgɯ ri pjɯ-nɯ-rku-j ɕti ma
trs: In order to prevent \forme{kɯpɤz} bugs from growing (in the meat), we buy refrigerators and put our meat in it.' (28-kWpAz, 46)

src: kɯrɯ-skɤt kɤ-βzjoz kɤ-nɯmga-t-a tɕe, mbarkʰom mɤɕtʂa jɤ-ɣe-a ŋu.
trs: I came all the way up to Mbarkham to learn the Gyalrong language.' (elicited)

src: mbarkʰom ju-ɣi-a nɯ, kɯrɯ-skɤt kɤ-βzjoz kɤ-nɯmga ŋu
trs: (The reason why) I come to Mbarkham is to learn the Gyalrong language.' (elicited)

src: tɯrme ra kɯ ɯ-<shipin> jo-lɤt-nɯ tɕe [nɯnɯ ɯ-kɤ-nɤmɲo] ɯ-spa jo-lɤt-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: People send him this video for him to watch it.' (conversation 2019-02-26)

src: [kɯrɯ-skɤt ɯ-kɯ-βzjoz] ɯ-spa, mbarkʰom mɤɕtʂa jɤ-ɣe-a ŋu.
trs: I came all the way up to Mbarkham to learn the Gyalrong language.' (elicited)

src: kɯ-ɣɤrʁaʁ ra kɯ tu-ndo-nɯ. [nɯ-kɯ-qur] tu-ndo-nɯ pjɤ-ŋgrɤl.
trs: (In former times), hunters would take (dogs to hunt). They would take dogs to help them (as their helpers).' (05-khWna, 39-40)

src: nɯnɯra kɯ tɕhi a-tɤ-stu-nɯ tɕe nɯ-tɯ-ci ɣɤʑu?
trs: What should they do in order to have water?' (divination 2005, 38)

src: lu-zɣɯt ɕɯŋgɯ tɕe nɯtɕu ku-ɣɤrat-a tɕetʰa a-mɤ-lɤ-zɣɯt
trs: Before it arrives, I will throw (the enchanted white stone), so that it does not arrive.' (25-kAmYW-XpAltCin, 62)

src: cʰa tɕi ko-tsʰi matɕi lo-βzi ɕti ri
trs: He had also drunk alcohol, since he was drunk.' (140506 loBzi, 13)

src: ɕɤxɕo pɤnmawombɤr jo-nɯ-ɣi ɯmɤ-kɯ-ŋu-ci ma, kʰa ɲɯ-ɣɤkʰɯ-nɯ
trs: Maybe Padma 'Od'bar came back the last few days, since there is smoke coming out from their house.' (Norbzang 2012, 226-227)

src: ma-jɤ-tɯ-ɕe ma tɯ-ndʐaβ
trs: Don't go (to the temple on the mountain to do circumambulations), you might fall down.' (conversation, conversation 15-12-05)

imt: \textsc{dem}  lie \textsc{neg}-\textsc{imp}-make[III]-\textsc{1sg} be.needed:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk} \textsc{lnk}   history record \textsc{ipfv}-2-make[III] be:\textsc{aff}:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk} later generations \textsc{erg}  \textsc{inv}-scold:\textsc{fact}-\textsc{1sg}-\textsc{pl}
src: nɯ kʰramba ma-tɤ-βze-a ra ma tɕe <lishijizai> pjɯ-tɯ-βze ɕti tɕetʰa, nɯnɯ rcanɯ <zuzubeibei> kɯ ɣɯ-nɤmqe-a-nɯ.
trs: I cannot tell lies, as   you are making a historical record, and previous and future generations would scold me.'  (27-kikakCi, 224)

src: a-mɤ-tʰɯ-sta ma tɕetʰa ju-nɯ-ɕe ɕti
trs: May she not wake up (Don't wake her up), otherwise she will go away.' (150818 muzhi guniang-zh, 106)

src: roʁre nɯ kɯnɤ [wuma ʑo kɯ-xtsʰɯm] mɤ-pe ma tɕe pjɯ-qlɯt-nɯ.
trs: As for fence rails also, it is not good (if they are) too thin, otherwise (the hybrid yaks in the cowshed) will break them.' (150902 mkhoN, 42)

src: ɯ-βri nɯra qapri ɯ-βri wuma ʑo ɲɯ-fse, ɯ-rme ri kɯ-tu maŋe. tɕeri ɯ-mɤlɤjaʁ ɣɤʑu.
trs: (The gecko's) body looks a little bit like the body of a snake, and it has also no hair. However, it has limbs.' (28-tshAwAre, 10)

src: kuwu nɯ iʑo kutɕu ji-ʑimkʰɤm tɕe tu ri mɤ-dɤn
trs: Bearded vultures are found here in our region, but not many.' (2011-08-kuwu, 28)

src: qaliaʁ nɯ to-z-nɯɣmaz ma kɤ-sat nɯ mɯ-pjɤ-cʰa
trs: He wounded the eagle, but could not kill it.' (150902 hailibu-zh, 21)

imt: pig \textsc{erg} too eat[III]:\textsc{fact} cow  \textsc{erg} too eat[III]:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk} people \textsc{inf}-eat  \textsc{contrast}:\textsc{foc}  \textsc{neg}-be.good:\textsc{fact}
src: paʁ kɯ tɕi ndze, nɯŋa kɯ tɕi ndze. tɕe [tɯrme kɤ-ndza] ndɤre mɤ-sna.
trs: Pigs eat it, cows eat it, but it is not good for people to eat.'  (17-ndZWnW, 125-126)

src: tɕe rɟɤlpu nɯ nɯ-rga jinbala zɯ ``e, a-tɕɯ ki stɤβtsʰɤt ci mɯ-ɕɯ-cʰa kɯ" ɲɤ-sɯso tɕe
trs: Although the king was happy (about that), he thought `I am worried that my son will not succeed in the contest.' (2003 sras, 84)

src: ``jɤ-ɣi" kɯnɤ mɤ-kɤ-ti kɯ, ``nɤ-rʑaβ ɣɯ-ku-βze-a" to-ti, rɟɤlpu nɯ ɯ-ɕki.
trs: Although (the king had not) said `come' (Without (the king) saying `come'), she told the king `I am coming to become your wife.'  (140511 yinzi-zh, 21)

src: pjɤ-kɯ-nɯβlu-a tɕe, nɯnɯ kɯ-pʰɤn sɤznɤ, mɤ́ɣrɤz a-mpʰɯz ɯ-ntɕʰɯr pa-nɯ-pʰɯt
trs: You cheated me, not only was (your healing method) not efficient (to treat my illness), but it took off a chunk of my bottom. (140427 qala cho kWrtsAG, 44)

src: ɕɤr tɕe ʑŋgri nɯ nɯ-mɤrʑaβ ʑo tɕe tɯ-kɤrme cʰɯ́-wɣ-rɤɕi ri, cʰɯ-kɯ-zri maŋe, mɤ́ɣrɤz ɲɯ-mŋɤm ma.
trs: In the night when there was a shooting star, we pulled our hair (thinking that our hair would grow longer), but not only (our hair) did not grow longer, (the only thing that it did) was hurt.' (29-mWBZi, 108)

src: aʑo ``nɯ ɕɯ tɯ-ŋu kɯ" nɯ-sɯso-t-a ri,  tɤ-mda tɕe nɤkinɯ, a-ftsa pjɤ-tɯ-ŋu
trs: I was wondering who you were, but it turns out that you are my nephew!' (150907 yingning-zh, 73-74)

src: ʑara χsɯm ma pjɤ-me-nɯ tɕe tɕendɤre nɯ-nɯŋa ci pjɤ-tu.
trs: They were only the three of them, and they had a cow. (07-deluge, 3)

src: ɯ-pʰoŋbu ra ɲɯ-wxti, ɲɯ-tsʰu ʑo.
trs: Its body is big and fat.' (26-GZo, 12)

src: mbro sɤznɤ ɲɯ-wxti. ɲɯ-mbro cʰo ɲɯ-wxti.
trs: It is larger than a horse. Higher and larger.'  (19-rNamoN, 15)

src: ɯ-ku nɯra rcanɯ, wuma ʑo ɲɯ-mpɕɤr cʰo kʰatoʁ ʑo ɣɤʑu
trs: Its head, it is very beautiful, and variegated.' (24-qro, 84)

src: tɕe nɯ ɯ-rɣi a-mɤ-pɯ-ɕe ra ma pjɯ-tsɣi mɤ-cʰa tɕe tɕendɤre a-nɯ-ɤci \textbf{ʑo} \textbf{qʰe} cʰo ftɕar a-kɤ-ndzoʁ \textbf{ʑo} \textbf{qʰe} li tu-ɬoʁ ɕti
trs: One should not let its grains go into (the ground), because they cannot rot, and when they get wet and the spring comes, they grow again.' (-08-qaJAGi, 48)

src: [ɕa] tɕi ɲɯ-ndze, [ɕɤci] tɕi ɲɯ-tsʰi, [tɤ-lu ta-mar] tɕi ɲɯ-ndze
trs: (Pigs) eat meat, drink meat stew, and also eat butter and have milk.' (05-paR, 30)

src: ɯʑo [pjɤ-mpɕɤr] ʁo alala ri, rɤɣo ri pjɤ-mkʰɤz, tɯ-rɟaʁ ri pjɤ-mkʰɤz.
trs: Not only was he good-looking, he was also expert at singing and dancing.' (160702 luocha-zh, 4)

src: [ɕɯ-mŋɤm] ɯ-tɤjɯ tɕe ɲɯ-sɤzoŋzoŋ ʑo ŋu
trs: Not only does (nettle sting) hurts, it also causes a numbing sensation.' (140428 mtshalu, 6)

src: tɯtsɣe ɯ-kɯ-βzu nɯ kɯ paχɕi mɯ-ɲɤ-mbi mɤra ma nɯ sɤznɤ to-nɤmqe tɕe jo-sɯx-ɕe.
trs: The merchant not only did not give him (any) apple, but instead scolded him and sent him away.' (150904 zhongli-zh, 15)

src: tɤ-mtʰɯm nɯra tu-ndze mɤkɯjɤɣ kɯ, ɯ-di ɲɯ-ɕɯ-mnɤm
trs: Not only does (the mouse) eat meat, it also makes it stinky.' (27-spjaNkW, 198)

src: tɕe [ɯ-rqʰu nɯ ɣɯrni] laʁma ɯ-ŋgɯ nɯ sɤjku cʰo ɲɯ-naχtɕɯɣ-ndʑi ri
trs: Apart from the fact that its bark is red, its inside is the same as that of the white birch.' (06-mbrAj, 13)

src: [kɤ-kɤ-pu kɤ-kɤ-sqa kɯ-fse nɯra mɤ-ndze] laʁma, nɯ ɯ-ro nɯ lonba tu-ndze ɕti.
trs: Apart from the fact that it does not eat food that has been baked or cooked, it eats everything else (=apart from cooked food, it eats everything else).' (19-GzW, 11)

src: wortɕʰi wojɤr ʑo tɕʰimaʁnɤ a-ɣi ra nɯ-pʰe ɕɯ-rɤfɕɤt-tɕi (tsaʁ) ma tɕetʰa ɣɯ-nɯzdɯɣ-a-nɯ
trs: Please, at least let the two of us go and inform my relatives, otherwise they will be worried about me.' (qachGa 2012, 76)

src: tɕʰimaʁ ``pɯ-tɯ-χɕu" tsaʁ tu-ti-a ma
trs: I (should) say at least `thank you'.' (2014-kWlAG, 624)

src: tɕe cʰɯ-βde-nɯ nɯmaʁnɤ fsapaʁ ɲɯ-mbi-nɯ ŋgrɤl ma
trs: (People uproot it) and either throw it away, or give it to the animals (to eat).' (12-Zmbroko, 120-122)

src: nɯmaʁnɤ tú-wɣ-nɯ-xsɯr, nɯmaʁnɤ <ban> tú-wɣ-βzu tɕe.
trs: People either fry it, or mix it in salad.' (conversation 14-05-10)
